{
  "texts": [
    "The size of the bubble is proportional to the frequency of the cluster's word occurrences, and its position is determined based on the cluster's Callon centrality and density.",
    "Callon centrality indicates the significance of the theme within the entire research area, while Callon density measures the theme's development.",
    "Consequently, thematic maps were generated to display the evolution of keyword trends, as illustrated in Fig. 8C.",
    "The thematic map is divided into four quadrants: The upper right quadrant highlights thematic keywords associated with motor themes, indicating well-developed topics related to the application of AI in breast cancer diagnosis, prognosis and treatment research.",
    "The second quadrant features niche themes that exhibit strong internal development."
  ]
}